<section id="service">
  <h2 id="service">Common AGA Appliance Problems We Repair</h2>
  <p>We repair many of the issues luxury homeowners commonly experience with <strong>AGA appliances</strong>, from classic cast iron systems to modern electric and control-based models. Our service is tailored to the specific appliance type, model series, and symptoms involved.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>AGA oven not heating or overheating:</strong> We diagnose heating performance issues, thermostat problems, temperature regulation faults, and components affecting cooking consistency.</li>
    <li><strong>AGA range cooker performance issues:</strong> If your AGA range is heating unevenly, taking too long to reach temperature, or no longer operating as expected, we inspect the relevant controls, heating systems, and related components.</li>
    <li><strong>Hotplate and burner problems:</strong> We address hotplates that are not heating correctly, burners that are not igniting properly, and gas-related issues on supported models.</li>
    <li><strong>AGA control and electrical faults:</strong> We service digital control issues, programming problems, temperature fluctuation concerns, and other electrical malfunctions affecting modern AGA units.</li>
    <li><strong>AGA Total Control, Dual Control, eR3, and eR7 issues:</strong> We diagnose model-specific performance problems, including delayed heat-up, inconsistent oven behavior, and control-related faults.</li>
    <li><strong>Ventilation and hood issues:</strong> We also service supported <strong>AGA hoods</strong> and related ventilation concerns that affect performance, airflow, and kitchen usability.</li>
    <li><strong>Maintenance-related performance decline:</strong> If your AGA is operating less efficiently over time, we inspect the appliance for buildup, wear, calibration concerns, and other maintenance-related issues.</li>
  </ul>
</section>

